<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="audience-n">audience <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'ɔːdiəns/    美 /'ɔːdiəns/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>观众；听众：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When Mozart’s music was performed in America, there was <strong>an audience of</strong> 100,000 people.
在美国演奏莫扎特的乐曲时，台下有10万观众。</p><footer>外研② – 3 改</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The lecture drew a large audience. 
这个讲座吸引了很多听众。</p></div>

<p>注: audience是集体名词，作主语时，如果作为整体看待，谓语动词用单数；如果强调各个成员，谓语动词用复数。  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The audience was large. 
观众很多。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The audience are dressed in a variety of ways. 
观众的穿着各不相同。</p></div></div>